          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Differential cross  sections for the reaction d(g,p)n",
                " have been determined at laboratory angles of 45, 75,",
                " 90,  and  135  degrees  for laboratory energies from",
                " approximately 50 to 90 MeV.  At each  of  the  above",
                " angles the energy spectrum of the recoil protons was",
                " determined  with   a   counter   telescope   and   a",
                " pulseheight  analysis system.  the low cross section",
                " for this reaction necessitates the reduction of  the",
                " background  to  a minimum.  This was accomplished by",
                " the use of a gaseous target and a particle selection",
                " technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
